- I started playing a bit with Heimdall[1], which provides a sort of self-hosted "application dashboard" which can be set as a browser's home or new tab page to provide quick-and-easy access to your most-used web apps and sites. Heimdall makes it simple to create shortcuts, but for certain "enhanced" apps[2] it can also pull live statistics from the app's API. I think that's pretty slick:
